Delete Your Account and Data

Overview
If you would like to delete your account and associated data from Bae Clinic, you can submit a request via email. Please note that account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone.


Steps to Request Account Deletion
To request the deletion of your account and all associated data, follow these steps:

Prepare an Email Request

Use your registered email address (the one linked to your Bae Clinic account).
Send an email to: baeclinicdev@gmail.com
Use the subject: Request for Account Deletion
Include the Following Information in Your Email

Full Name: [Your Name]
Registered Email: [Your Email Address]
Reason for Account Deletion (optional)
Confirmation Statement:
"I request the permanent deletion of my Bae Clinic account and all associated data. I understand that this action is irreversible."

Wait for Confirmation

Our support team will process your request within 7-14 business days.
You will receive a confirmation email once your account has been deleted.

Types of Data Deleted and Retained

Permanently Deleted Data:
- Account credentials
- Personal Information (Name, Email, Phone Number, Address, National ID Number)

Data That May Be Retained:
- Payment records and invoices (for tax and compliance purposes)
- Customer support interactions (for dispute resolution)

After the retention period, any remaining data will be completely erased from our system.


Additional Information
If you have an active subscription, cancel it first before submitting a deletion request to avoid unwanted charges.
Once deleted, your account cannot be recovered. If you wish to use our services again, you will need to create a new account.
If you have any issues, feel free to contact our support team.
For more details, visit our Privacy Policy: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/baeclinic/baeclinic/refs/heads/main/privacy_policy
